That covers the banking system; 
          and
         one of the elements of the banking system which is important in this is to follow banking regulations which, in very simple terms, require people to identify the source of large sums of money which they are depositing in the banking system.

You can argue about the adequacy of the City of London's regulation; 
          but
         the Isle of Man authorities, as one example, are very keen to ensure that is the case.

